If you run the clean_snapshot script without parameters, it will run
interactively.

You can run the script with no interaction by passing the --force, -f, or 
-pt (passthrough) flag and the pool's name.

Example: # clean_snapshots -f rpool


This is an example crontab. I will use mine as an example:

# Run a scrub every week
00 05 * * 0 /usr/local/sbin/zpool_scrub rpool

# Take a snapshot twice a day
00 00,12 * * * /usr/local/sbin/zfs_snapshot rpool

# Check the pool health twice a day
00 00,12 * * * /usr/local/sbin/check_zfs_pool

# Clean snapshots once a month
05 01 01 * * /usr/local/sbin/clean_snapshots -f rpool
